asons (1062 isolates), revealing higher genotypic richness on walls compared to bats and a stable frequency of multilocus genotypes over multiple winters. This clearly implicates hibernacula walls as the main environmental reservoir of the pathogen, from which bats become reinfected annually during the autumn.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Fischer, Nicola M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Altewischer, Andrea", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ranpal, Surendra", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Dool, Serena", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kerth, Gerald", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Puechmaille, Sebastien J.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/ab41e9a5a6dd5a29bd0f86a47d81394d", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/e85a89627dca58e55f96d2d5f481895a0b4a09d10f5ecb6aa2d9bdc477000b11", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/WVAM9XKZ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/WVAM9XKZ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/9da8cd9be4a905426e96a678a11f37f2!/b77953-80514", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "2", "pages": "675-690", "title": "Molecular Ecology", "volume": "31"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/ab41e9a5